ObAgent: uncertain.

Analysis: multiple services show increased request latencies and some success-rate/count drops, while top component-level anomalies include both container network receive MB and container fs_writes on node-5. That could come from either heavy disk write I/O or network problems. To disambiguate, check:
- whether_is_abnormal_metric for container/node disk write throughput and latency (node.disk.write_bytes, node.disk.write_time, container.fs_write_latency/IOPS) and host iowait;
- whether_is_abnormal_metric for network retransmits/errors (interface.tx/rx_errors, tcp_retransmits, net.if.in.err) and packet-drop counters;
- collect_trace on slow RPCs to see whether spans wait on network (socket) vs kernel I/O (write).
JudgeAgent: No - The run ended with an 'uncertain' hypothesis. The trace/metric scan lists multiple anomalous components (e.g., high container.network_receive_MB.eth0 and container.fs_writes./dev/vda on node-5 and latency spikes across many services) but no single location was selected, no one anomaly type from the closed set was committed, no concrete root-cause KPI/log was declared as the official reason, and no exact occurrence minute was pinned. Therefore the root cause is not fully identified.

